SEARCH
Package com.simulation.model

Class SimulationConfig

java.lang.Object
com.simulation.model.SimulationConfig
public class SimulationConfig extends Object
Configuration parameters for the simulation.

This class holds all configurable parameters for the simulation, including:

  • Service times for each service point
  • Number of CPU and GPU compute nodes
  • Task arrival rate and probabilities
  • User type distribution
  • Simulation duration

All parameters have default values and can be modified through setter methods.

Version:
2.0
Author:
Cloud Simulation Team

    • getEnterpriseVipProbability

      public double getEnterpriseVipProbability()
      Gets the Enterprise VIP user probability.

      This is calculated as: 1.0 - normalUserProbability - personalVipProbability to ensure probabilities sum to 1.0.

      Returns:
      the Enterprise VIP probability

    • setEnterpriseVipProbability

      public void setEnterpriseVipProbability(double v)
      Sets the Enterprise VIP user probability.

      This method adjusts normalUserProbability to maintain total probability = 1.0.

      Parameters:
      v - the Enterprise VIP probability (0.0 to 1.0)
